headline: 3 Brilliant High-Yield Stocks to Buy Now and Hold for the Long Term
summary: The stock market has declined this year, yet it still offers just a paltry 1.3% dividend yield.  The average dividend yield of stocks in the S&P 500 index (SNPINDEX: ^GSPC) is just 1.3% or so today, even though the index fell into correction territory earlier in 2025.  If you are a dividend investor in search of high yields, now is a time to focus on industry-leading companies like Toronto-Dominion Bank (NYSE: TD), Prologis (NYSE: PLD), and NNN REIT (NYSE: NNN).
